quran[54]{c,v,t}:
  70,19,Verily man is formed impatient
  70,20,"When evil toucheth him, he is bewailing"
  70,21,And when good toucheth him he is begrudging
  70,22,Not so are the prayerful
  70,23,Who are at their prayer constant
  70,24,And those in whose riches is a known right
  70,25,For the beggar and the destitute
  70,26,And those who testify to the Day of Requital
  70,27,And those who are fearful of their Lord's torment
  70,28,Verily the torment of their Lord is not a thing to feel secure from
  70,29,And those who of their private parts are guards
  70,30,Save in regard to their spouses or those whom their right hands own; so verily they are not blameworthy
  70,31,"And whosoever seeketh beyond that, then it is those who are the trespassers"
  70,32,And those who of their trusts and their covenant are keepers
  70,33,And those who stand firm in their testimonies
  70,34,And those who of their prayer are observant
  70,35,"Those shall dwell in Gardens, honoured"
  70,36,"What aileth those who disbelieve, toward thee hastening"
  70,37,"On the right and on the left, in companies"
  70,38,"Coveteth every man of them, that he shall enter the Garden of Delight"
  70,39,By no means! veriiy We! We have created them from that which they know
  70,40,"I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests, that, vierly We are Able"
  70,41,To replace them by others better than they; and We are not to be outrun
  70,42,Wherefore let thou them alone plunging in vanity and sporting until they meet their Day which they are promised
  70,43,"The Day whereon they shall come forth from the sepulchres hastily, as though they were to an altar hurrying"
  70,44,Downcast shall be their looks; abjectness shall overspread them. Such is the Day which they are promised
  71,1,"Verily We! We sent Nuh Unto his people saying: warn thy people ere there come Unto them torment afflictive"
  71,2,"He said: O my people! verily I am Unto you a warner manifest"
  71,3,"Worship Allah, and fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive you your sins, and will defer you to an appointed term. Verily the term of Allah when it cometh shall not be deferred, if ye but knew"
  71,5,"He said: my Lord! verily have called my people night and day"
  71,6,And my calling hath only increased them in fleeing
  71,7,"And verily so oft as I call them, that Thou mayest forgive them, they place their fingers into their ears, and wrap themselves with their garments, and persist, and are stiff-necked"
  71,8,Then verily have called Unto them publicly
  71,9,"Then verily spake Unto them openly, and secretly also I addressed them"
  71,10,"And I said: ask forgiveness of your Lord; verily He is ever Most Forgiving"
  71,11,He will send the heaven upon you copiously
  71,12,And He will add Unto you riches and children and will appoint Unto you gardens and will appoint Unto you rivers
  71,13,What aileth you that ye expect not in Allah majesty
  71,14,And surely He hath created you by stages
  71,15,Behold ye not in what wise Allah hath created seven heavens in storeys
  71,16,"And hath placed the moon therein for a light, and hath made the sun a lamp"
  71,17,And Allah hath caused you to grow from the earth as a growth
  71,18,"And thereafter He will cause you to return thereinto, and He will bring you forth a forthbringing"
  71,19,And Allah hath made the earth Unto you an expanse
  71,20,That of it ye may traverse the ways open
  71,21,Nuh said. my Lord! verily they have disobeyed me and followed them whose riches and children have only increased them in loss
  71,22,And who have plotted a tremendous plot
  71,23,"And who have said: ye shall not leave your gods; nor Shall ye leave Wadd nor Suwa', nor Yaghuth, nor Ya'uq nor Nasr"
  71,24,And surely they have misled many. And increase Thou these wrong-doers in naught save error
  71,25,"And because of their misdeeds they were drowned, and then they were made to enter a Fire. Then they found not for themselves, beside Allah, any helpers"
  71,26,"And Nuh said: my Lord! leave not upon the earth of the infidels one inhabitant"
  71,27,"Verily if Thou shouldst leave them, they Will mislead Thine bondmen and will beget not save sinning infidels"
  71,28,"My Lord! forgive me and my parents and him who entereth my house as a believer, and believing men and believing women, and increase not the wrong-doers in aught save ruin"